        <p>Rep. Mike Doyle (D-PA):  &#8220;Maybe mash-ups are transformative new art that expands the consumers experience and doesn&#8217;t compete with what an artist has made available on iTunes or at the CD store.  And, I don&#8217;t think Sir Paul [McCartney] asked for permission to borrow that bass line, but every time I listen to that song, I&#8217;m a little better off for him having done so.&#8221;</p>

